column2: System of a Down - Hypnotize (Quick Ship)
column3:
Released as the companion to Mezmerize, Hypnotize captures System of a Down at their most direct and restless: riff-heavy songs that lurch from tight, staccato verses into wide-open choruses, then pivot again without warning. ‘Attack’ and ‘Kill Rock ’n Roll’ hit fast, while ‘Tentative’ and ‘Holy Mountains’ stretch into moodier, melodic spaces. Even when the band leans into dark humour (‘Vicinity of Obscenity’, ‘She’s Like Heroin’), the playing stays precise—drums snapping, guitars cutting, vocals trading urgency for melody. It closes with ‘Soldier Side’, tying the album back to its twin release with a blunt, unresolved finish.
